to the editor william safire mentions scriptural admonitions as in the doomed city of sodom as an argument against governmentally sanctioned gay marriage column dec 1 let 's ignore for a moment the fact that many mainstream clergy in the major judeo christian denominations support the legalization of gay marriage and already perform religious same sex commitment ceremonies the more fundamental problem with mr safire 's reasoning is that the bible is not a valid basis for legal arguments in a society that adheres to the separation of church and state many many fine americans hindus buddhists and atheists to cite just three examples do not accept the bible as the basis for their religious beliefs and practices are these citizens feelings about gay marriage any less valid or any less american than those of jews christians or muslims thomas l james new york dec 1 2003

